Class IntervalTreeMain

  • java.lang.Object
    • IntervalTreeMain

  • public class IntervalTreeMain
extends java.lang.Object
    THIS CLASS IS PROVIDED TO STUDENTS AND WILL NOT BE SUBMITTED
    -- DO NOT EDIT THIS CLASS

    This is the main file which runs the program. It has two modes to run:

    Interactive mode: java IntervalTreeMain 1

    Non-Interactive mode: java IntervalTreeMain 2 data_01.txt

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Run as a stand-alone application.
        Parameters:
        args - first argument indicates mode (1 for interactive or 2 for non-interactive);

        If mode is 2, the second argument is name of a comma separated file text file with interval ranges.

      • nonInteractiveMode

        public void nonInteractiveMode(java.lang.String filename)
        Runs the program in non-interactive mode with a data file of pre-determined intervals. Reads the interval data from the file data_01.csv and constructs the interval tree, then runs several insert/delete/overlap queries.

        The format of each line of the data file is:

        interval_start,interval_end,interval_label

        Example:

         16,60,p9
 11,37,p8
 26,62,p7
 31,47,p6
 11,48,p5
 38,43,p4
 25,26,p3
 3,28,p2
 4,46,p1
 3,16,p0
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of a csv file where each row represents one interval and is specified in form: start_time,end_time,interval_label

      • interactiveMode

        public void interactiveMode()
        Runs the program in interactive mode where user can input operation on command line. Use this mode to iteratively build the program and debug it using the TreeViewer. 
         1. Insert Schedule
 2. Delete Schedule
 3. Find Overlapping Schedules
 4. Schedules Containing Point
 5. Print Tree Stats
 6. Show Tree Viewer
 7. Quit Program
 Enter Choice:
